{"name":"README - Dynamic Custom Dice","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Make your Own Dice","type":"text","_id":"7eUWZM6rC3aPdOYb","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>This module let you change the faces of the dice without need to code.</p><p></p><h2>1 - Create the Dice Art</h2><p>You need to create your art. You can download the templates and edit them with <a href=\"https://www.gimp.org/\">GIMP</a> or Photoshop.</p><p>Download Templates: <a href=\"https://github.com/brunocalado/dynamic-custom-dice/tree/main/docs/templates\">link</a></p><p>You need to create one image for each dice face (<strong>label</strong>). There is two optional extra kind of images you can also do for each side <strong>bump</strong> and <strong>emission</strong>. If you don't want to add a new face you can use <strong>dummy</strong>.</p><ul><li><p>Label: It's the image of the side.</p></li><li><p>Bump: This image try to simulate depth. White color will make the image move towards the screen.</p></li><li><p>Emission: This image emit light. The color black will have no light. Paint with the desired color.</p></li><li><p>Dummy: This will use a number instead of a image.</p></li></ul><p>It's recommended to use webp for your images, but you can use PNG instead.</p><p></p><h2>2 - Name and Folder</h2><p>You need to put your files in a Foundry VTT valid path. It can be anywere inside Foundry VTT Data Folder.</p><p>You <strong>MUST</strong> use the standard naming: <strong>NUMBER_IMAGE-TYPE.</strong></p><p>Examples:</p><ul><li><p>1_label: This would be the image for dice face 1.</p></li><li><p>1_bump: This would be the bump for dice face 1.</p></li><li><p>1_emission: This would be the emission for dice face 1. If you just want one face to have emission, you still need to add um emission file to each face. Just use a empty image.</p></li><li><p>20_dummy: This will not add the image. This will use the a simple label.</p></li><li><p>09_label: This would be the image for dice face 9. You must add an zero to dices with more then 8 faces. So, the d10 names would be: 01_label, 02_label, 03_label, â€¦, 10_label.</p></li></ul><p>Put all your images for one dice inside a folder. <strong>Don't add any other file to this folder!</strong></p><p></p><p>This example replaces all faces from a d6:</p><img src=\"modules/dynamic-custom-dice/docs/docs_dice_names.webp\" /><p></p><p>This example replaces just the 20 from the d20:</p><img src=\"modules/dynamic-custom-dice/docs/docs_d20_dummy.webp\" /><p></p><h2>3 - Update the Dice</h2><p>Run this macro and pick your dice folder and the dice type. It'll update the dice and reload the world.</p><p></p><h2>4 - Select the Dice</h2><p>Now, go to Dice so Nice settings and pick the dice you made. Done.</p><img src=\"modules/dynamic-custom-dice/docs/docs_dsn_settings.webp\" /><p></p><h2>5 - Suggestion</h2><p>Increase the dice size to better enjoy your dice.</p><img src=\"modules/dynamic-custom-dice/docs/docs_dsn_scale.webp\" /><p></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.6bRtjmcwV3yIBVNT"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pbta","systemVersion":"0.6.1","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666635932995,"modifiedTime":1666709812263,"lastModifiedBy":"nr0OZJqbaeegsb5R"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"nr0OZJqbaeegsb5R":3},"_id":"kzsawN8cZN3WfV7X"}
